## Controller Patterns

### Full Page Controller
```java
@Controller
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class ClaimsListController {

    private final DebtServiceClient debtServiceClient;
    private final PortalSessionService sessionService;

    @GetMapping("/fordringer")
    public String claimsList(Model model, HttpSession session) {
        UUID creditorId = sessionService.resolveActingCreditor(null, session);
        if (creditorId == null) {
            return "redirect:/demo-login";
        }
        model.addAttribute("creditorId", creditorId);
        return "claims/claims-list";
    }
}
```

### HTMX Fragment Controller
```java
@GetMapping("/api/claims/recovery")
public String claimsTableFragment(
        @RequestParam(defaultValue = "0") int page,
        @RequestParam(defaultValue = "claimId") String sortBy,
        Model model, HttpSession session) {

    var claims = debtServiceClient.listClaims(creditorId, page, sortBy);
    model.addAttribute("claims", claims);
    return "claims/fragments/claims-table :: claimsTable";
}
```

Fragment endpoints:
- Return `"{template-path} :: {fragment-name}"` (Thymeleaf fragment selector)
- Are called by `hx-get` / `hx-post` in templates
- Return HTML fragments, NOT full pages (no layout wrapping)

## HTMX Template Patterns

### Progressive Loading (load data after page shell renders)
```html
<div id="claims-table-container"
     hx-get="/{{service}}/api/claims/recovery"
     hx-trigger="load"
     hx-indicator="#claims-loading"
     aria-live="polite">
    <div id="claims-loading" class="skat-loading htmx-indicator"
         role="status">Indlæser…</div>
</div>
```

### Search/Filter (HTMX form submission)
```html
<form hx-get="/{{service}}/api/claims/recovery"
      hx-target="#claims-table-container"
      hx-indicator="#claims-loading">
    <input type="text" name="searchQuery"
           th:placeholder="#{claims.search.placeholder}" />
    <button type="submit" class="skat-btn">Søg</button>
</form>
```

### Sorting (inline link)
```html
<a hx-get="/{{service}}/api/claims/recovery"
   hx-vals='{"sortBy":"receivedDate","sortDirection":"desc"}'
   hx-target="#claims-table-container">
    Received Date ▼
</a>
```

## Accessibility Requirements (WCAG 2.1 AA)

All portal pages MUST:
- Use semantic HTML (`<main>`, `<nav>`, `<thead>`, `scope="col"`)
- Include skip-to-content links
- Set `aria-live="polite"` on HTMX swap targets
- Set `role="status"` on loading indicators
- Use `th:aria-label` for interactive elements
- Load `a11y.js` for focus management after HTMX swaps
- Use skat-design-system components (`.skat-btn`, `.skat-table`, `.skat-card`)

## WebClient Service Clients

```java
@Component
public class DebtServiceClient {
    private final WebClient webClient;

    public DebtServiceClient(
            WebClient.Builder builder,
            @Value("${opendebt.services.debt-service.url}") String baseUrl) {
        this.webClient = builder.baseUrl(baseUrl).build();
    }

    @CircuitBreaker(name = "debt-service", fallbackMethod = "fallback")
    @Retry(name = "debt-service")
    public RestPage<ClaimListItemDto> listClaims(UUID creditorId, int page, String sortBy) {
        return webClient.get()
            .uri(b -> b.path("/api/v1/claims/recovery")
                .queryParam("creditorId", creditorId)
                .queryParam("page", page)
                .queryParam("sortBy", sortBy)
                .build())
            .retrieve()
            .bodyToMono(new ParameterizedTypeReference<RestPage<ClaimListItemDto>>() {})
            .block();
    }
}
```

All clients use `@CircuitBreaker` + `@Retry` (Resilience4j) with empty-result fallbacks.

## TDD Cycle (mandatory)

### Unit Tests (Controller)
```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class ClaimsListControllerTest {
    @Mock private DebtServiceClient debtServiceClient;
    @Mock private PortalSessionService sessionService;
    @InjectMocks private ClaimsListController controller;

    @Test
    void claimsList_redirectsToLogin_whenNoSession() {
        when(sessionService.resolveActingCreditor(eq(null), any()))
            .thenReturn(null);
        Model model = new ConcurrentModel();
        String view = controller.claimsList(model, new MockHttpSession());
        assertThat(view).isEqualTo("redirect:/demo-login");
    }

    @Test
    void claimsTableFragment_returnsFragmentRef() {
        when(sessionService.resolveActingCreditor(any(), any()))
            .thenReturn(UUID.randomUUID());
        when(debtServiceClient.listClaims(any(), anyInt(), any()))
            .thenReturn(new RestPage<>(List.of(), 0, 20, 0, 0));
        Model model = new ConcurrentModel();
        String view = controller.claimsTableFragment(0, "claimId", model, new MockHttpSession());
        assertThat(view).isEqualTo("claims/fragments/claims-table :: claimsTable");
    }
}
```

### Template Assertions (Cucumber)
```java
@Then("the list page uses the SKAT standardlayout")
public void theListPageUsesTheSkatStandardlayout() throws IOException {
    String html = readResource(templateResource);
    assertThat(html).contains("layout:decorate=\"~{layout/default}\"");
}

@Then("the table body is loaded asynchronously via HTMX")
public void theTableBodyIsLoadedAsynchronouslyViaHtmx() throws IOException {
    String html = readResource(templateResource);
    assertThat(html).contains("hx-get");
